FWIW, to sort of put all my other comments together, I think this entire function could be rewritten as:

```

  stepTyped(fob: Fob, step: number) {
    let newLinkedTime = {...this.linkedTime};
    if (fob === Fob.START) {
      newLinkedTime.start = {step};
    } else if (fob === Fob.END) {
      newLinkedTime.end = {step};
    }

    if (
      newLinkedTime.end !== null &&
      newLinkedTime.start.step > newLinkedTime.end.step
    ) {
      // Start is now greater than end - flip them.
      newLinkedTime = {
        start: newLinkedTime.end,
        end: newLinkedTime.start,
      };
    }

    this.onSelectTimeChanged.emit(newLinkedTime);
  }
```

Some advantages are:
No need to early return.
Only single place where you might call emit().
Only single place where values are checked if they need to be swapped and are swapped.

